pt: {sc}regular{/sc} {sc}normal{/sc} {sc}typical{/sc} {sc}natural{/sc} mean being of the sort or kind that is expected as usual, ordinary, or average. {sc}regular{/sc} stresses conformity to a rule, standard, or pattern.
{sc}normal{/sc} implies lack of deviation from what has been discovered or established as the most usual or expected.
{sc}typical{/sc} implies showing all important traits of a type, class, or group and may suggest lack of strong individuality.
{sc}natural{/sc} applies to what conforms to a thing's essential nature, function, or mode of being.

pt.t: the {it}natural{/it} love of a mother for her child
